                <path
                  stroke-linecap="round"
                  stroke-linejoin="round"
                  d="M15 12a3 3 0 11-6 0 3 3 0 016 0z"></path>
              </svg>
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-4">
              Customizable Rules
            </h3>
            <p class="text-text-muted leading-relaxed">
              Set custom rotation rules based on your team's needs. Configure
              priority, weights, and distribution logic to match your workflow.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Background grid pattern -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 opacity-[0.03] pointer-events-none">
      <svg width="100%" height="100%" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg">
        <defs>
          <pattern
            id="features-grid"
            width="32"
            height="32"
            patternUnits="userSpaceOnUse"
          >
            <path
              d="M 32 0 L 0 0 0 32"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1"></path>
          </pattern>
        </defs>
        <rect width="100%" height="100%" fill="url(#features-grid)"></rect>
      </svg>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction Section -->
  <section class="py-20 bg-background">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-display font-bold text-text mb-6">
          Fair Meeting Distribution for Teams
        </h2>
        <div
          class="prose prose-lg max-w-none space-y-6 text-text-muted leading-relaxed"
        >
          <p>
            Round robin scheduling automatically distributes incoming meetings
            evenly across your team members. When someone books an appointment
            through your scheduling link, CalendHub assigns it to the next
            available team member in rotation. This creates perfectly balanced
            workload distribution without anyone manually assigning meetings or
            managing schedules.
          </p>

          <p>
            Sales teams use round robin to ensure every lead gets distributed
            fairly. Support teams use it to balance customer calls across
            representatives. Recruiting teams use it to distribute candidate
            interviews evenly. Any team that receives inbound meeting requests
            benefits from automatic fair distribution that prevents overload and
            ensures everyone contributes equally.
          </p>

          <p>
            The system respects individual availability when assigning meetings.
            If the next person in rotation is unavailable at the requested time,
            CalendHub automatically moves to the next available team member.
            This means meetings always get assigned to someone who can actually
            attend, while still maintaining overall fairness in distribution
            over time.
          </p>

          <p>
            Round robin assignment happens instantly when meetings are booked.
            The assigned team member receives the calendar invite and all
            meeting details automatically. Team members can see their assigned
            meetings in their personal calendars, and managers can track
            distribution patterns to ensure balanced workload across the entire
            team.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How It Works Section -->
  <section class="py-32 relative overflow-hidden">
    <div class="container relative z-10">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Badge -->
        <div
          class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-orange-500/10 border border-orange-500/20 rounded-full px-4 py-2 text-sm font-medium text-orange-600 dark:text-orange-400 mb-6"
        >
          <svg
            class="w-4 h-4"
            fill="none"
            viewBox="0 0 24 24"
            stroke="currentColor"
            stroke-width="2"
          >
            <path
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
              d="M13 10V3L4 14h7v7l9-11h-7z"></path>
          </svg>
          <span>How It Works</span>
        </div>

        <!-- Heading -->
        <h2
          class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl lg:text-6xl font-display font-bold mb-6 text-text"
        >
          Automatic Round Robin
          <br />
          <span class="text-text-muted">In Three Simple Steps</span>
        </h2>

        <!-- 3 Step Cards -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 mb-12">
          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <div class="group relative">
            <div
              class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-500/20 to-amber-500/20 rounded-3xl blur-xl opacity-0 group-hover:opacity-100 transition-opacity duration-500"
